    "#### looping over a dictionary"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A `for` loop over a dictionary iterates over the keys."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "skip-execution"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "apple\n",
      "banana\n",
      "orange\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fruit_inventory = {\"apple\" : 6,\n",
    "        \"banana\" : 2,\n",
    "        \"orange\" : 4}\n",
    "\n",
    "for f in fruit_inventory:\n",
    "    print(f)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " If we want the values as well, we can use `[dict_name].items()`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "skip-execution"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "('apple', 6)\n",
      "('banana', 2)\n",
      "('orange', 4)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fruit_inventory = {\"apple\" : 6,\n",
    "                \"banana\" : 2,\n",
    "                \"orange\" : 4}\n",
    "\n",
    "for f in fruit_inventory.items():\n",
    "    print(f)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To separate each (key, value) tuple, we can provide to variables to the for loop. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "skip-execution"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fruit_inventory = {\"apple\" : 6,\n",
    "                \"banana\" : 2,\n",
    "                \"orange\" : 4}\n",
    "\n",
    "for fruit_name, quantity in fruit_inventory.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"There are {quantity} {fruit_name}s in stock.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
